Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the technical aspects of cloud computing, which involves distributed and parallel computing. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper mentions the low cost of cloud computing, which can be related to the computational complexity of cloud-based applications. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses various cloud-based applications, including enterprise resource planning, supply chain management, and customer relationship management, which are all related to software engineering. 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper mentions business applications that can be deployed on the cloud, which may involve databases. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the potential of cloud computing to reach millions of users, which is related to networking and internet architecture.
